      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Robert von Ranke Graves (1895-1985) was an English poet, novelist, critic and classicist.  He was a prolific author, producing historical fiction (<emph render="italic">I, Claudius</emph>, <emph render="italic">King Jesus</emph>, <emph render="italic">Count Belisarius</emph>, literary analysis and criticism (<emph render="italic">The White Goddess</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Reader Over Your Shoulder </emph>), translations of classical works (<emph render="italic">The Rubaiyyat of Omar Khayyam</emph>, <emph render="italic">The Golden Ass</emph>) and more than forty collections of poetry.  His mother Amalie was a great-niece of the noted German historian Leopole von Ranke.</p><p>Letters in the collection from Graves address Robert Reynolds as "cousin."</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Robert Reynolds Collection Relating to Robert Graves</emph> contains incoming correspondence, clippings and a photograph.  The first three letters are from Robert Graves to Robert Reynolds; the remainder are from various people to Reynolds about Graves.  One of the letters from Graves claims Claus von Stauffenberg, one of the leaders of the plot to assassinate Adolf Hitler in 1944, as another cousin.  The clippings are of Graves' obituary in English and German press, and a photograph of his grave.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
